The following account of Soltre, from Father R. Augustin Hay's “ Scotia Sacra.,” an unpublished work, compiled in the year 1700,3 may be quoted, as furnishing some minute particulars regarding the Hospital and its loca· lity which are not elsewhere to be met with. He commits, however, a palp- able mistake in saying that David, Earl of Huntingdon, was buried at Soltre in 1219. The words in the Scotichronieon to which Hay evidently refers, apud abbatiam de ,Santrez‘a sepultus,4 unquestionably apply to Sawtrey‚ a Cistereian abbey in Huntingdonshire.
